  "prompt": "How do you put on fake eyelashes without glue?",
  "response": "Putting on fake eyelashes without glue can be achieved using alternative methods such as magnetic lashes or adhesive liner. Here are steps for both options:\n\n### Magnetic Lashes\n\n#### Materials Needed:\n- Magnetic eyelashes\n- Tweezers (optional)\n\n#### Steps:\n1. **Prepare Natural Lashes:** Curl your natural lashes and apply mascara if desired. This helps blend the magnetic lashes with your natural ones.\n2. **Align Magnetic Lashes:** Take the magnetic lashes and gently bend them to fit your eye shape.\n3. **Top Magnetic Lash:** Hold the top magnetic lash close to your natural lash line. You can use tweezers or your fingers.\n4. **Bottom Magnetic Lash:** Align the bottom magnetic lash under your natural lashes. When the magnets from both strips meet, they will snap together, securing the lashes in place.\n5. **Adjust if Necessary:** Ensure the lashes are comfortable and properly aligned. You can reposition them if needed.\n\n### Adhesive Liner\n\n#### Materials Needed:\n- Adhesive eyeliner\n- Fake eyelashes\n- Tweezers (optional)\n\n#### Steps:\n1. **Prepare Natural Lashes:** Curl your natural lashes and apply mascara if desired.\n2. **Apply Adhesive Liner:** Shake the adhesive liner well and apply it along your lash line just like you would a regular eyeliner.\n3. **Let it Dry:** Allow the adhesive liner to become tacky. This usually takes around 30 seconds.\n4. **Apply Fake Lashes:** Using tweezers or your fingers, place the fake lashes directly onto the adhesive liner, starting from the inner corner moving to the outer corner.\n5. **Secure and Adjust:** Press the lashes lightly along the lash line to ensure they are firmly attached. Adjust if necessary to ensure proper alignment.\n\nThese methods offer alternatives to traditional lash glue and can provide a secure hold for your fake lashes without the mess.",
